The Commonwealth of Massachusetts
_______________
In the One Hundred and Ninety-Fourth General Court
(2025-2026)
_______________
An Act authorizing the town of Stoughton to exempt all Stoughton police officers at all ranks
from civil service.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Notwithstanding any general or special law to the contrary, all of the
2 positions of all police officers in all ranks in the police department of the Town of Stoughton,
3 excluding the Chief of Police previously exempted through the Massachusetts Acts of 1978,
4 Chapter 474, shall be exempt from Chapter 31 of the General Laws.
5 SECTION 2. Section 1 of this act shall not impair the current civil service status of any
6 person holding a position as a sworn member of the police department of the Town of Stoughton
7 on the effective date of this act and only shall be applied to appointments and promotions
8 prospectively as of the date of the Annual Town Meeting vote of May 8, 2024.
9 SECTION 3. This act shall take effect upon passage.
